               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa nǝfq “Book of the Assistant Priest” (fols. 4r-26r)
 I-1)
                     Prayer of oblation (fols. 4r-6v l.1): excerpt from the Liturgy of Catechumen
                     (MQ, Śǝrʿatä qǝddase, ch. III, §§ 41-44). 
 I-2) Fǝtḥat za-wald “Absolution
                     of the Son” (fols. 6v l.2-10r l.3): excerpt from the Liturgy of Catechumen (MQ,
                     Śǝrʿatä qǝddase, ch. III, §§ 56-65). 
 I-3) General absolution (fols. 10r
                     l.4-12r l.7): excerpt from the Liturgy of Catechumen (MQ, Śǝrʿatä qǝddase, ch.
                     III, §§ 61-65). 
 I-4) Concluding chant after the reading from the Pauline
                     Epistles (fols. 12r l.8-14r l.7): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Word (MQ,
                     Śǝrʿatä qǝddase, ch. III, §§ 132-135). 
 I-5) Universal prayer by the
                     assistant priest (fols. 14r l.8-17r l.3): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Word
                     (MQ, Śǝrʿatä qǝddase, ch. III, §§ 194-209). 
 I-6) Prayer of blessing of St
                     Basil (fols. 17r l.4-21r l.1): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Eucharist,
                     Anaphora of the Apostles (MQ, Qǝddase za-ḥawāryāt, §§ 10-21). 
 I-7)
                     Supplication for peace, the hierarchy and the assembly (fols. 21r l.2-22v):
                     excerpt from the Liturgy of the Word (MQ, Śǝrʿatä qǝddase, ch. IV, §§ 15-21).
                     
 I-8) Prayer of intercession following the imposition of the celebrant‘s
                     hand (fols. 23r-26r): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Eucharist, Anaphora of
                     the Apostles (MQ, Qǝddase za-ḥawāryāt, §§ 154-157).</summary>
